column1: #Text=—A little smack called the Zouave, of Ryde, Isle of Wight, 43 tons burden, foundered in the St.
#Text=Albans Race, some six miles from the Head, at about half-past five on Tuesday morning, the 6th inst.
#Text=She was bound from Portland to Ryde, laden with Portland block ; and, when off the place indicated, she encountered a heavy sea, in which she sank.
#Text=The crew, consisting of the captain, Mr.

#Text=Thomas Dallimore, who is the sole owner, and another seaman, made their escape in the boat, which was almost swamped on nearing the shore; but, by the assistance of the coastguard, the poor fellows were landed in safety in Chapmans Pool, near the wreck of the Georgina.
#Text=They were taken to a house belonging to one of the coastguard, where their wants were carefully attended to.
#Text=The captain has been running his little craft to and from Portland for ten years past; but she is not insured.
#Text=Up to the present moment the Georgina remains in pretty much the same condition as when she was cast upon the rocks.
#Text=Had the wind and sea, which sunk the Zouave, continued, her destruction would most likely have been completed.
#Text=All the cargo of any value has been removed.
